<subSubSection id="C3306EE7FFE9FF93FF6CFEF1FD4C9FE7" pageId="5" pageNumber="561" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B953D6CFFE9FF93FF6CFEF1FCDB9F0F" blockId="5.[151,1437,152,503]" box="[199,782,260,287]" pageId="5" pageNumber="561">
<emphasis id="B95EE17EFFE9FF93FF6CFEF1FE9B9F0F" bold="true" box="[199,334,261,287]" pageId="5" pageNumber="561">Host plant:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C2A46EFFFE9FF93FEFEFEF1FD549F0F" authority="(Baker)" baseAuthorityName="Baker" box="[341,641,260,287]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vitaceae" genus="Cissus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Vitales" pageId="5" pageNumber="561" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tweedieana">
<emphasis id="B95EE17EFFE9FF93FEFEFEF1FDF09F0E" box="[341,549,260,287]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="561">Cissus tweedieana</emphasis>
(Baker)
</taxonomicName>
(dead vine).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B953D6CFFE9FF93FF6CFEDCFD4C9FE7" blockId="5.[151,1437,152,503]" pageId="5" pageNumber="561">
<emphasis id="B95EE17EFFE9FF93FF6CFEDCFE009F53" bold="true" box="[199,469,296,323]" pageId="5" pageNumber="561">Taxonomic discussion:</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A46EFFFE9FF93FC80FEDCFB5C9F53" authority="Bates, 1870" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1870" box="[811,1161,296,323]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Obrium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="561" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cordicolle">
<emphasis id="B95EE17EFFE9FF93FC80FEDCFC2F9F52" box="[811,1018,296,322]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="561">Obrium cordicolle</emphasis>
Bates, 1870
</taxonomicName>
, in which the elytra also bear dark-rimmed setae-bearing punctures, but the two last elytral bands make up a large transverse-oval ring also touching the suture (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB409DFFE9FF93FED2FE85FD7B9F9B" author="Hovore, F. T. &amp; Chemsak, J. A." box="[377,686,368,395]" pageId="5" pageNumber="561" pagination="31 - 54" refId="ref5892" refString="Hovore, F. T. &amp; Chemsak, J. A. (1980) A review of the Mexican and Central American species of Obrium Dejean (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 34 (1), 31 - 54." type="journal article" year="1980">Hovore and Chemsak 1980</bibRefCitation>
: fig 10), while in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A46EFFFE9FF93FCC4FE85FBD29F9A" authorityName="Zubarán" authorityYear="2020" box="[879,1031,368,395]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Obrium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="561" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trilobatum">
<emphasis id="B95EE17EFFE9FF93FCC4FE85FBD29F9A" box="[879,1031,368,395]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="561">O. trilobatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the third band at the irregular edges, and does not come together in the suture. (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBB409DFFE9FF93FDD2FE61FC759FBF" author="Hovore, F. T. &amp; Chemsak, J. A." box="[633,928,404,431]" pageId="5" pageNumber="561" pagination="31 - 54" refId="ref5892" refString="Hovore, F. T. &amp; Chemsak, J. A. (1980) A review of the Mexican and Central American species of Obrium Dejean (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae). The Coleopterists Bulletin, 34 (1), 31 - 54." type="journal article" year="1980">Hovore &amp; Chemsak 1980</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 10). It is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A46EFFFE9FF93FB42FE60FE499FC3" authority="Zajciw, 1965" authorityName="Zajciw" authorityYear="1965" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Obrium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="561" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrifasciatum">
<emphasis id="B95EE17EFFE9FF93FB42FE60FED19FC3" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="561">Obrium quadrifasciatum</emphasis>
Zajciw, 1965
</taxonomicName>
bears dark punctures on the elytra, and has a fourth band curved as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2A46EFFFE9FF93FB01FE4DFA979FC2" authorityName="Zubarán" authorityYear="2020" box="[1194,1346,440,467]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Obrium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="561" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trilobatum">
<emphasis id="B95EE17EFFE9FF93FB01FE4DFA979FC2" box="[1194,1346,440,467]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="561">O. trilobatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the second band is disposed in a different pattern.
</paragraph>
